InfoViz Project 1 on Maps

Air Quality Spatial Variations

Vijay Kumar and Muhammad Rashid

12/06/2022

The project 1 is focused on visualization of PM\(_{2.5}\) concentrations and Air Quality index (AQI) on US map.

library(readr)
library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(lubridate)

Data collection:

The data was collected from US EPA database at https://aqs.epa.gov/aqsweb/airdata/download_files.html.

Pre-Processing: Renaming variable is important in R coding, space in letters or large names create problem.

pmaqi <- 
  pmaqi %>%
  dplyr::select(`State Name`, `County Name`, `Site Num`, `Date Local`,
         `Arithmetic Mean`, AQI, Longitude, Latitude) %>%
  filter(`Arithmetic Mean` >= 0) %>%
  drop_na()
names(pmaqi) <- c("statename", "countyname", "sitenum", "date", 
                     "pm25", "aqi",  "long", "lat")

Data Summary: Lets look if we find summary statistics of PM\(_{2.5}\) based on states. The whole idea is coming from the fact that annual average PM\(_{2.5}\) should be less than \(12 \frac{ug}{m^3}\) according to EPA standards [1].

a<-pmaqi%>%
  dplyr::group_by(statename)%>%# Summary by group using dplyr
  dplyr::summarize(
    n=n(),
    min = round(min(pm25),1),
    q1 = quantile(pm25, 0.25),
    median = round(median(pm25),1),
    mean = round(mean(pm25),1),
    q3 = quantile(pm25, 0.75),
    max = round(max(pm25),1),
    sd=round(sd(pm25,na.rm = TRUE),1))

## aggregate for point data
### for pm2.5
a <- 
  pmaqi %>%dplyr::select(sitenum, long, lat, pm25, aqi) %>%
  group_by(sitenum) %>%
  summarise(pm25 = mean(pm25), aqi = mean(aqi), long = mean(long), lat = mean(lat)) %>%
  gather(key = class, value = value, -long, -lat, -sitenum) %>%
  filter(long > -125)
a1 <- a[a$class == "pm25", ]
ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group),
               fill = "white", colour = "gray50", size = 0.3, data = states) +
  geom_point(aes(x = long, y = lat, color = value, size=3), data = a1) +
   #geom_text(data=States, aes(long, lat, label = state_abbv), size=2)+
  scale_color_distiller("PM 2.5", palette = "RdYlGn")+
  geom_path(size = 0.1)+theme_bw()+
  geom_text(data=centroids, aes(x=long,y=lat, group=NA, label=abb), 
          size=3, vjust=0.8, hjust=0.8)+xlab("Longitude")+ylab("Latitude")+theme(
            # LAIDES APPEARANCE
            plot.title = element_text(size=14, face= "bold", colour= "black" ),
            axis.title.x = element_text(size=14, face="bold", colour = "black"),    
            axis.title.y = element_text(size=14, face="bold", colour = "black"),    
            axis.text.x = element_text(size=12, face="bold", colour = "black"), 
            # axis.text.y = element_text(size=12,  colour = "black"), # unbold
            axis.text.y = element_text(size=12, face="bold", colour = "black"), # bold
          )

#County data setup with counties population more than 1M

library(lubridate)
#round dates down to week
df<-pmaqi
df$year <- floor_date(df$date, "year")
df$State<-state.abb[match(df$statename, state.name)]
df<-df %>%
  group_by(sitenum,year,statename,countyname,long,lat, State) %>%
  summarize(pm25 = mean(pm25), aqi=mean(aqi))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'sitenum', 'year', 'statename', 'countyname', 'long',
'lat'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
df$abbr<-state.abb[match(df$statename, state.name)]
df<-df%>%dplyr::rename(county=countyname)
df<-merge(df,countypop,by=c("county","abbr"))

Creating choropleth maps of good, and bad:unhealthy for sensitive group air quality days were there as defined by EPA [2].

## aggregate aqi by state (areal level)
states <- map_data("state")
aqi$State <- stringr::str_to_lower(aqi$State)
a <- 
  aqi %>%
  dplyr::select(State, `Good Days`, `Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups Days`,`Hazardous Days`) %>%
  group_by(State) %>%
  summarise(good = mean(`Good Days`),
            unhealthy = mean(`Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups Days`),
            hazardous = mean(`Hazardous Days`))
a <-
  states %>%
  left_join(a,  by = c("region" = "State"))

ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group, fill = good),
               data = a) +
  scale_fill_distiller("Days", palette = "Spectral",direction = 1) +
  xlab("Longitude") + ylab("Latitude") +
  ggtitle("Distribution of good days") +
  geom_path(size = 0.1)+theme_bw()+coord_map()+
  geom_text(data=centroids, aes(x=long,y=lat, group=NA, label=abb), 
          size=2.8, vjust=0.8, hjust=0.8)+xlab("Longitude")+ylab("Latitude")+theme(
            # LAIDES APPEARANCE
            plot.title = element_text(size=14, face= "bold", colour= "black" ),
            axis.title.x = element_text(size=14, face="bold", colour = "black"),    
            axis.title.y = element_text(size=14, face="bold", colour = "black"),    
            axis.text.x = element_text(size=12, face="bold", colour = "black"),
